General Information
===================

mysmartctl is a simple yet powerful tool to control the mySmartUSB controller.
It supports all commands implemented by mySmartUSB MK2 v2.11. Should work for
controllers with an older firmware as well.
mysmartctl also implements a basic terminal to use mySmartUSB's data mode
aka RS232-Pass-Through mode.

mysmartctl is free software released under the MIT License, see the file
"LICENSE" for more information.

Requirements
============

mysmartctl requires ncurses [1].
As its build requirements it also needs an ANSI C99 capable 
compiler like GCC [2].

  [1] http://www.gnu.org/software/ncurses/
  [2] http://gcc.gnu.org

Installation
============

To install mysmartctl you can use a prebuilt package for your
distribution or you can use the GNU built systen.

  $ ./configure
  $ make
  # make install

For more information check INSTALL.

